No, there are two ways to do it. just like throughout the code you see
tf.nn.something

that would work, and you would get rid of the import tensorflow.models.rnn.

and what that means is that it is placed in tensorflow.python.ops

so I just replaced tensorflow.models.rnn with tensorflow.python.ops
